subject: Re: [Read_Alphabet] Migration to Groups.io.
msgSnippet: Hi, Paige--Is everybody who was on the Yahoo groups site automatically going to be on the new site as well? On Fri, Oct 25, 2019 at 7:44 PM Paige Gabhart
messageBody:
Hi, Paige--Is everybody who was on the Yahoo groups site automatically going to be on the new site as well?



On Fri, Oct 25, 2019 at 7:44 PM Paige Gabhart paige@... [Read_Alphabet] <Read_Alphabet@yahoogroups.com> wrote:
 

Hello to all Read_Alphabet members,

This may be a duplicate message that you receive.  A previous message I
attempted to send while logged in to Read_Alphabet seems to be MIA. 
Perhaps, that is just Yahoo.  Who knows?

The migration of Read_Alphabet to Quikscript@... is underway.  It
will take several days apparently.

I approved the groups.io bot and upgraded it to a moderator and told it
to start the transfer.

I paid $220.00 for a premium account for a year.  Some people have
kindly offered to help share that cost.

I was looking at Paypal and found their money pool, which allows groups
of people to pay into a pool.  So I set one up.  If people use their
Paypal accounts to pay a small amount such as $3-$5, then this could be
spread out so nobody is out that much.  Once we reach $200.00 I will
shut it down.

Here is the link if you are willing to contribute to keep the group
messages and data online and available.

https://paypal.me/pools/campaign/112531338612568873

Sincerely,

Paige Gabhart
